<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="224" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1736,2087]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,373,1736,1762]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Distribution:—</emphasis>
Endemic to the Rio Chico Valley between Chuquichuqui and Imillahuanusca, especially near Zurima, Prov. Oropeza, Dept. 
<collectingRegion box="[475,609,1772,1798]" country="Bolivia" name="Chuquisaca" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Chuquisaca</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[619,705,1772,1798]" name="Bolivia" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation box="[716,781,1772,1799]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1632,1654]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1608]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,190,1608]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Map showing location of Euploca riochiquensis in Chuquisaca in the Rio Grande catchment area of Bolivia’s central Andean valleys." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479375/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="225" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1736,2087]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1452,158,1085]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="225" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1808,1834]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Habitat:—</emphasis>
Very locally frequent in sparse xerophytic scrub with abundant 
<taxonomicName authority="(Steud.) Seigler &amp; Ebinger (2006)" authorityName="Seigler &amp; Ebinger" authorityYear="2006" baseAuthorityName="Steud." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senegalia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gilliesii">
<emphasis box="[1063,1265,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Senegalia gilliesii</emphasis>
(Steud.) 
<bibRefCitation author="Seigler, D. S. &amp; Ebinger, J. E." pageId="5" pageNumber="224" pagination="48 - 93" refId="ref5153" refString="Seigler, D. S. &amp; Ebinger, J. E. (2006) American species of Senegalia. Phytologia 88 (1): 48 - 93. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 17845" type="journal article" year="2006">Seigler &amp; Ebinger (2006)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
on steep rocky slopes in the Rio Chico Valley, some 
<quantity box="[947,1061,1844,1871]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" unit="km" value="12.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="10.0">10–15 km</quantity>
above its confluence with the Rio Grande, principally, perhaps exclusively, on sandstone, between about 1600 and 
<quantity box="[1047,1135,1881,1907]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" unit="m" value="1900.0">1900 m</quantity>
. The area is not particularly diverse in terms of species numbers but is very interesting in terms of endemism. As well as the new species, 
<taxonomicName authority="L. B. Sm." authorityName="L. B. Sm." class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Puya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ugentiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Puya ugentiana</emphasis>
L.B.Sm.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, L. B." box="[364,499,1952,1979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" pagination="84 - 161" refId="ref5274" refString="Smith, L. B. (1966) Notes on Bromeliaceae XXIII. Phytologia 13: 84 - 161. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21846" type="journal article" year="1966">Smith 1966</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="L. B. Sm." authorityName="L. B. Sm." box="[518,754,1952,1979]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Puya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis box="[518,653,1952,1978]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Puya valida</emphasis>
L.B.Sm.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, L. B." box="[768,904,1952,1979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" pagination="454 - 488" refId="ref5239" refString="Smith, L. B. (1964) Notes on Bromeliaceae XXII. Phytologia 13: 454 - 488. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21852" type="journal article" year="1964">Smith 1964</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Epling &amp; Jativa (1966)" authorityName="Epling &amp; Jativa" authorityYear="1966" box="[923,1446,1952,1979]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Salvia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graciliramulosa">
<emphasis box="[923,1180,1952,1978]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Salvia graciliramulosa</emphasis>
Epling &amp; Játiva (1966)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="L. Hrom." authorityName="L. Hrom." box="[136,452,1988,2015]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Tillandsia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="helmutii">
<emphasis box="[136,348,1988,2014]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Tillandsia helmutii</emphasis>
L.Hrom.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hromadnik, L." box="[467,664,1988,2015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" pagination="63 - 65" refId="ref4227" refString="Hromadnik, L. (1990) Tillandsia helmuttii L. Hromadnik, spec. nov. Bromelie 1990 (3): 63 - 65." type="journal article" year="1990">Hromadnik 1990</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="L. Hrom." authorityName="L. Hrom." box="[684,1026,1988,2015]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Tillandsia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oropezana">
<emphasis box="[684,921,1988,2014]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Tillandsia oropezana</emphasis>
L.Hrom.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hromadnik, L." box="[1040,1235,1988,2015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" pagination="14 - 17" refId="ref4201" refString="Hromadnik, L. (1989) Tillandsia oropezana L. Hromadnik spec. nov. Bromelie 1989 (1): 14 - 17." type="journal article" year="1989">Hromadnik 1989</bibRefCitation>
) are other pinpoint endemics growing on the same formation in the same area. Other Bolivian endemic species occurring in the same dry valley include 
<taxonomicName authority="Harms (1908)" authorityName="Harms" authorityYear="1908" box="[299,743,2060,2087]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Brongniartia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulbrichiana">
<emphasis box="[299,581,2060,2086]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Brongniartia ulbrichiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Harms, H. A. T." box="[586,743,2061,2087]" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" pagination="88 - 97" refId="ref4097" refString="Harms, H. A. T. (1908) Legumnosae andinae. In I. Urban, Plantae novae andinae imprimis Weberbauerianae IV. Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 42: 88 - 97." type="journal article" year="1908">Harms (1908)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cardenas) Van Scheepen (1997: 18)" authorityName="Van Scheepen" authorityPageNumber="18" authorityYear="1997" baseAuthorityName="Cardenas" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Hippeastrum" kingdom="Plantae" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="225" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mollevillquense">
<emphasis box="[754,1082,2060,2086]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="224">Hippeastrum mollevillquense</emphasis>
(Cárdenas) Van 
<bibRefCitation author="Scheepen, J. van" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="225" pageId="5" pageNumber="224" refId="ref5096" refString="Scheepen, J. van (1997) In: Meerow, A. W., Van Scheepen, J. &amp; Dutilh, J. H. A. Transfers from Amaryllis to Hippeastrum (Amaryllidaceae)." type="book" year="1997">Scheepen (1997: 18)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lindau) Wassh. &amp; C. Ezcurra (1997)" authorityName="Wassh. &amp; C. Ezcurra" authorityYear="1997" baseAuthorityName="Lindau" box="[186,850,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="consanguinea">
<emphasis box="[186,435,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">Justicia consanguinea</emphasis>
(Lindau) Wassh. &amp; C.Ezcurra (1997)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Goyder (2008)" authorityName="Goyder" authorityYear="2008" box="[861,1257,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Funastrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rupicola">
<emphasis box="[861,1084,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">Funastrum rupicola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Goyder, D. J." box="[1090,1257,158,184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" pagination="331 - 333" refId="ref4049" refString="Goyder, D. J. (2008) Funastrum rupicola (Apocynaceae: Asclepiadoideae), a new species from Bolivia. Kew Bulletin 63: 331 - 333. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 008 - 9019 - 9" type="journal article" year="2008">Goyder (2008)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Benth. (1848)" authorityName="Benth." authorityYear="1848" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Salvia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orbignaei">
<emphasis box="[1267,1451,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">Salvia orbignaei</emphasis>
Benth. (1848)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="J. R. I. Wood (2007)" authorityName="J. R. I. Wood" authorityYear="2007" box="[315,676,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Salvia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sucrensis">
<emphasis box="[315,450,195,221]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">S. sucrensis</emphasis>
J.R.I. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, J. R. I." box="[513,676,194,220]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" pagination="177 - 222" refId="ref5766" refString="Wood, J. R. I. (2007) The Salvias (Lamiaceae) of Bolivia. Kew Bulletin 62: 177 - 222. [https: // www. jstor. org / stable / 20443346]" type="journal article" year="2007">Wood (2007)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Gentry ex J. R. I. Wood (2008)" authorityName="J. R. I. Wood" authorityYear="2008" box="[692,1236,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Tecoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="beckii">
<emphasis box="[692,857,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">Tecoma beckii</emphasis>
A.Gentry ex J.R.I. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, J. R. I." box="[1072,1236,194,220]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" pagination="143 - 172" refId="ref5807" refString="Wood, J. R. I. (2008) A Revision of Tecoma Juss. (Bignoniaceae) in Bolivia. Botanical Journal of the Linnaean Society 156: 143 - 172. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.2007.00731. x" type="journal article" year="2008">Wood (2008)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="H. Hrom." authorityName="H. Hrom." class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Tillandsia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lotteae">
<emphasis box="[1252,1451,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">Tillandsia lotteae</emphasis>
H.Hrom.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rauh, W." box="[251,377,230,256]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" pagination="263 - 266" refId="ref5075" refString="Rauh, W. (1978) Tillandsia lotteae. Journal of the Bromeliad Society 28: 263 - 266." type="journal article" year="1978">Rauh 1978</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="J. S. Miller &amp; J. R. I. Wood" authorityName="J. S. Miller &amp; J. R. I. Wood" box="[442,965,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cordiaceae" genus="Varronia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lantanifolia">
<emphasis box="[442,680,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">Varronia lantanifolia</emphasis>
J.S.Miller &amp; J.R.I.Wood
</taxonomicName>
, but all of these occur in other locations in the inter-Andean dry valley system of central Andean 
<collectingCountry box="[738,824,266,292]" name="Bolivia" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. The Río Grande Valley and its tributaries the Río Chico and Río Grande are remarkable for the presence of scattered, narrowly restricted endemics from many plant families. An earlier publication (
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, J. R. I." box="[398,532,338,364]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" pagination="249 - 260" refId="ref5858" refString="Wood, J. R. I. (2013) Bonamia (Convolvulaceae) in Bolivia. Kew Bulletin 68: 249 - 260." type="journal article" year="2013">Wood 2013</bibRefCitation>
) has drawn attention to the endemics found in Puente Santa Rosa area, while this paper highlights one of the side valleys, the Río Chico valley in 
<collectingRegion box="[855,986,374,400]" country="Bolivia" name="Chuquisaca" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">Chuquisaca</collectingRegion>
as an important centre of endemism.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,410,436]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Found in flower towards the end of the summer rainy reason, all collections of flowering material having been made in March.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1435,482,509]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,1085]" box="[189,1435,482,509]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,356,482,508]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; P. Munoz Wood" authorityYear="2022" box="[490,641,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riochiquensis">
<emphasis box="[490,641,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">riochiquensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the Río Chico, to whose valley the species is endemic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="225" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,610,518,544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">Preliminary conservation status:—</emphasis>
As far as it is known, this species is restricted to a limited area of the Rio Chico Valley in 
<collectingRegion box="[320,454,554,580]" country="Bolivia" name="Chuquisaca" pageId="6" pageNumber="225">Chuquisaca</collectingRegion>
. All collections have been made close to the Sucre-Cochabamba highway and no search has been made at any distance from this road. As the steep scrub-covered slopes on various geological formations including sandstone extend over huge botanically unexplored areas, there is no reason to believe this species is as rare as the few records might suggest. Equally, there are no obvious threats to this habitat from mining, deforestation or human settlement and even goats do not seem to find this species particularly palatable. Until systematic search has been made in suitable areas in the same general region, this species can only be realistically assessed as Data Deficient (DD) according to 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[348,499,770,796]" pageId="6" pageNumber="225" refId="ref4254" refString="IUCN (2019) Guidelines for using the IUCN red list categories and criteria, version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Committee of the IUCN Species Survival Commission." type="book" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
guidelines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
